## F4 — LOW (Leg 2 — claim vs. enforcement) — final-test overlap guard cannot fire under normal flow

`discovery_run.py:151` `_validate_discovery_does_not_overlap_final_test` checks
`discovery_bars["SessionDate_ET"].max() > splits["validation_end"]`. But
`discovery_bars` is sliced as `SessionDate_ET <= splits["discovery_end"]`, and
`discovery_end <= validation_end` by construction in `chronological_session_splits`.
So `max()` is always `<= discovery_end <= validation_end` and the guard can never
trip in normal operation. It is a defensive assert against a hypothetical
mis-slice, which is fine — but the cycle-6 framing that it "catches partial
overlap with the final-test window" overstates what it mechanically does. No
action required beyond not relying on it as real final-test protection; if real
protection is wanted, the check belongs at the point a caller chooses the slice
bound, not after the bound has already excluded the test window.

